<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October 11,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 285.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith for your
                                information a copy of a letter from the American Board of
                                Commissioners for Foreign Missions in relation to the massacre of
                                the missionaries and their families connected with the board, in the
                                province of Shansi, and the participation of the governor of the
                                province in the deed.</p>
                            <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>